    <fr:title text="Quasi-compact continuous maps">Quasi-compact continuous maps</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
  We say a continuous map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : Y \to  X]]></fr:tex> between topological spaces is <html:em>quasi-compact</html:em> if the inverse image of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> preserves compact opens. This is mainly useful when <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X,Y]]></fr:tex> are both <fr:link href="/topl-VV9N/" title="Spectral spaces" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-VV9N/" display-uri="topl-VV9N" type="local">spectral</fr:link>.
</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
