          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  More generally, we say a morphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : Y \to  X]]></fr:tex> of <fr:link href="/schm-86OJ/" title="Scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-86OJ/" display-uri="schm-86OJ" type="local">schemes</fr:link> is <html:em>quasi-compact</html:em>, if the underlying continuous map is <fr:link href="/topl-9BKS/" title="Quasi-compact continuous maps" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-9BKS/" display-uri="topl-9BKS" type="local">quasi-compact</fr:link>.
</html:p>
